# Next.js App Router Structure

This project uses Next.js 15 with the App Router. Here's how the app directory is structured:

## Key Files and Conventions

- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx): Root layout with global UI elements
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx): Main homepage component (route: /)
- [src/app/google/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/google/page.tsx): Google-inspired page (route: /google)
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css): Global styles with Tailwind

## Routing

- Each folder under app/ becomes a route segment
- page.tsx files define the UI for a route
- layout.tsx files define shared UI for child routes
- API routes are defined in app/api/ folders with route.ts files

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS 4 is used for styling
- Global styles are imported in the root layout
- Components use utility classes for styling
